      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T22:20:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When I read exact, I think that this will perform historical lookups and find the sensor values at a specific time-- but since we don\u0027t store historical data, that\u0027s not true.  Instead, it will be valid for from the last setTarget event (if there\u0027s a new setTarget, the result will be invalid).  Implementing historical lookups to support this seems overkill :-)\n\nIs there something else we can do that won\u0027t have this connotation?\n\nLooking at the rest of the review, it looks like this is used to make sure the position/rotation for the virtual camera is at the same time.  Perhaps we could have an option like PARAMETER_VALUE_LAST_UPDATE, and a separate helper to explicitly perform an update @now?  Although there\u0027s a small chance that an update will happen in between position/rotation getters...\n\nAnother idea would be to have a helper that returns position+rotation together.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 44,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "c8f5a4bb41f4a2b770c3dc768bb9003951b94fe4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
